{
  "stem": "14613.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we went to the synagogue with our father, which was a very large, very beautiful, large synagogue.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this we went only during the holidays.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not only the high holidays, like Yom Kippur or Rosh Hashanah, but we did go to the minor holidays too, whether it was Passover or Hanukkah, and so on.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We did have a very traditional Jewish home because these holidays-- and really, I remember it the best, like, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] like Passover, where we had the whole family around the table.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And by whole family, I don't mean only our immediate family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But most of the time, we had my mother's brother and his family.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They were more-- or they were less Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So they used to come always to us because maybe my mother wouldn't eat there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we always had the, the, the Seder, which was a lot of people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we had-- we were playful as children, of course.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I remember this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This was something that sticks in my mind more than many other things.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The same thing was Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We would play.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We would light the candles.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My father liked and enjoyed, very much, when we were singing Hebrew song.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And this is another difference, which I am sorry we don't have in the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "That when I went to school-- in our school, in addition to, to studying Hebrew, we have learned different songs that go with the holidays, whether it was for Hanukkah, for Passover, or whatever it is, and also songs-- generally, Hebrew songs.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Which I have noticed that children here, when they go to Hebrew school and so on, they don't study it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And yet, in my humble opinion, these are the things-- they stay with me.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
